        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We require two pointed observations at the positions of the sources B1-bS and B1-bN. In configuration 5 of Band 7, the maximum spatial resolution is 0.22". Taking into account the declination of the objects (~+31°) we predict a degradation of the spatial resolution such that we expect a beam of the order of 0.4" (based on the ALMA user manual). At the distance of the sources (~235 pc) this corresponds to less than 100 AU, a resolution high enough to reach our scientific objectives.
The sources are so bright that the sensitivity is not an issue: the time estimator predicts a SNR of more than 80 for an on-source integration time of 60 s. The sources are extended at 345 GHz but we have access to other data (SCUBA-2) that will allow us to recover the filtered-out emission, so we do not need additional ACA observing time.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
